extends java.util.AbstractSet<se.miun.itm.input.model.Document>
implements se.miun.itm.input.aspects.Exportable, se.miun.itm.input.aspects.Identifiable
    A Framework is a Set of code-mapping Document:s.
    Author:
    Stefan Karlsson

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      private static class  Framework.DocumentWrapper
      A DocumentWrapper wraps a code-mapping document in order to provide references to the framework to which it belongs and to the next and previous element in the framework's linked sequence of DocumentWrapper:s.

        public Framework(java.lang.String id,
         se.miun.itm.input.model.Document... documents)
        Constructs a Framework with the specified ID. Each given document is added to this framework provided that it's a well-formed code-mapping document that isn't already part of another framework.
        Parameters:
        id - The ID of this framework.
        documents - Code-mapping documents to be added to this framework.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the ID is already taken, or if any of the documents isn't a well-formed code-mapping document.

      • release

        public static boolean release(java.lang.String id)
        Releases the specified framework, making it inaccessible via the getInstance method. In addition, all elements are removed from it and any subsequent attempt to add new elements will result in an IllegalStateException.
        Parameters:
        id - The ID of the framework that shall be released.
        Returns:
        true if the framework was released, or false if there was no framework with the given ID.

      • releaseAll

        public static void releaseAll()
        Releases all frameworks, making them inaccessible via the getInstance method. In addition, all elements are removed from them and any subsequent attempt to add new elements to any of them will result in an IllegalStateException.

     for (Iterator it = myFramework.iterator(); it.hasNext();) {
